html: 4.12.25  8:28 pm   i get a weird mix of awe and jealousy when i see people making things sometimes. because sometimes you come across people that are amazing at a whole bunch of different creative things, like making music, and drawing, and writing stories, etc. meanwhile, i'm sitting here trying to be good at just one of those things, and still not managing to get anywhere close. and it makes me feel inspired, because those people are awesome and cool, but also kind of defeated, because i feel like whatever i make will always be bad in comparison. and i know you're not supposed to compare yourself to other people, that you just have to focus on improving on your own work. but it's hard for me to do that, because i want to see what other people do so i can learn from it. so, how do i learn from others without comparing myself to them? i just feel so frustrated having all these ideas for things i want to do and make and never being able to execute them in a way that lives up to other people.
